<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Validibot test fixture: a well-formed Peppol BIS Billing 3.0 (UBL) invoice
  that PASSES the illustrative en16931_subset.sch (zero ERROR findings) but
  trips ONE WARNING.

  It is identical to peppol_invoice_valid.xml except the supplier's
  cbc:EndpointID has NO schemeID attribute, which fires the advisory rule
  VB-EAS-01 (flag="warning"). Totals still reconcile
  (TaxExclusive 100.00 + TaxAmount 21.00 = TaxInclusive 121.00), a line and a
  currency code are present, so no fatal rule fires.

  Expected: error_count == 0, warning_count == 1 (VB-EAS-01), passed == True —
  the invoice-domain counterpart to purchase_order_warnings_only.xml, proving
  the D3 "passes with warnings" rule on the flagship domain too.

  Hand-built fixture, not a real invoice or a conformance sample.
-->
